text: All I can say is that it is one of the best university plaza (or letâ€™s say it as communal area) I have ever visited. It has a plenty of food options from cheap stuffs to expensive one, and what I appreciate the most is it has a plenty of halal food options.

Feels like a mall in the midst of the university campus, filled with young and energetic students! With birds chirping and all the greeneries. Vibrant, lots of retail outlets, McDonals, Subway, Mr Bean, Prime Supermarket, etc. Wow, such a beautiful campus!

It is a square in the campus of Nanyang Technological University where are lots of places to eat and some shopping. On the second floor you can find a place named North Space Food court with several restaurants with a huge variety of kinds of food such as Chinese, Indian, Italian, etc. Pay attention you have not pay with cash on the restaurants if you haven't on of acceptable cards as NETS or NTU students cards you will have to buy (I think is free with more then 10,00) and load this one right there.
Once a car park now a plaza. Many tables for students to eat, chat, study, and socialize. Could be quite warm during afternoon.
Nice open space with plenty of food.
